flowRoot.flowPara: A little bit about my self.
One of the driving forces in my life is the thirst for knowledge and new skills, especially if there is a challenge. Craftsmanship, precision and doing something right is a passion.
These traits fuel my desire to go further, beyond my current abilities.

Since a very early age I have been fascinated how things work, and that hunger sparked interest in varying fields, such as computer science and electronics, and over the years I have gathered a toolkit of knowledge and experience.

Collaboration with other people, as well as teaching and helping others are one of my strong suites. I am strong believer in Open Source software, and agile methodologies. I started and maintain Arduino-CMake, an Open Source project, with 10 active contributors.
Have a look at my work at https://github.com/queezythegrat/, it should demonstrate some of my skills.

Art, design and creativity is also ingrained in me, simplicity is better than complexity, beauty is better than ugly, and my work tries to convey that. Nature and science is built on simple concepts layered on top of each other, and I strive to mimic that simplicity.
